TextEng: "Goodbye."
"Yes, and what about his priesthood."
"Think what you wish. What do I care?"
"Vix'thra was always dead. But yes, he is no more."
Text: "빅스트라는 항상 죽어 있었어. 하지만 그래, 이제 없어."

TextEng: "Look, I got what I came for and I'm going home."
Text: "봐, 내가 온 이유는 달성했고 집으로 갈 거야."

TextEng: "Any vengeance will be mine. They die tonight."
Text: "복수는 내 몫이야. 그들은 오늘 밤 죽어."

TextEng: "Then you'd best do something about that, hadn't you..."
Text: "그럼 그에 대해 네가 뭔가 하는 게 좋겠지..."

TextEng: "Goodbye."
"Ha. Do you think I did it to please you?"
Text: "하. 내가 널 기쁘게 하려고 한 것 같아?"

TextEng: "It's true, but the god he worshiped remains."
"Yes, no more Ceremonies for Drearing's Deep."
Text: "그래, 음울한자의 협곡을 위한 의식은 이제 없어."

TextEng: "Hey, I freed you from the High Priest. You handle the rest."
Text: "이봐, 대사제로부터 널 풀어줬어. 나머지는 네가 처리해."

TextEng: "If you don't like it, then go back to being slaves!"
"What do you want me to do?"
"Goodbye."
"You're scared of the priests, aren't you."
"Picking?"
"How does a Ceremony get called?"
"Who runs this place?"
"And who does the picking?"
"Why is his name the only one spoken?"
"Picked for what?"
"Can you tell me a little about this village?"
"Slaves?"
"It's all right. You have nothing to worry about."
"What do you have to worry about?"
"Do you have a name?"
"Who says you shouldn't give names?"
"Well my name's <FullName>. Now how hard was that?"
"What do you mean, 'next one picked'?"
